      "id": "PopularPost321294",
      "post_content": "The more obvious problem with this is that Modular only helps artifact creatures. For this to be used to its fullest, you need to be playing a lot of artifact creatures AND multiple colours. Although the Vivid lands were printed, getting anywhere more than 3 colours is going to be a chore.  \n  \nIn limited, 3 colours isn't that odd to play around. However, sometimes you just can't get that 3rd land, and are stuck playing with just 2 of your 3 colours, even on turn six. What do you do then? Do you make a 2/2 for ![6](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=6&type=symbol), or do you wait until the next turn, hoping to get that 3rd colour? It's just one of the problems of Limited that you have to work around. [Empty the Warrens](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Empty the Warrens) works just the same: do you wait for a cheap spell to add on 2 more tokens, or just work with 2 1/1 tokens for ![3](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=3&type=symbol)![Red](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=R&type=symbol)?  \n  \nAll in all, this is either above average or absolutely worthless. ",
      "posted_by": "Ferlord",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost321294\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_post\">The more obvious problem with this is that Modular only helps artifact creatures. For this to be used to its fullest, you need to be playing a lot of artifact creatures AND multiple colours. Although the Vivid lands were printed, getting anywhere more than 3 colours is going to be a chore.<br/><br/>In limited, 3 colours isn't that odd  to play around. However, sometimes you just can't get that 3rd land, and are stuck playing with just 2 of your 3 colours, even on turn six. What do you do then? Do you make a 2/2 for <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"6\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=6&amp;type=symbol\"/>, or do you wait until the next turn, hoping to get that 3rd colour? It's just one of the problems of Limited that you have to work around. <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Empty the Warrens\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Empty the Warrens\">Empty the Warrens</a> works just the same: do you wait for a cheap spell to add on 2 more tokens, or just work with 2 1/1 tokens for <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"3\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=3&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Red\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=R&amp;type=symbol\"/>?<br/><br/>All in all, this is either above average or absolutely worthless. </span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl01_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '321294'); return false;\">\r\n                         